Hardening = making your server more secure. A script can do things like:
1. Disable unnecessary services.
2. Create a non-root user.
3. Configure a firewall.

Example script:
#!/bin/bash
# harden.sh
# Disable unused services (example: ftp)
systemctl disable vsftpd 2>/dev/null
# Create a new non-root user
NEWUSER="secureuser"
if ! id "$NEWUSER" &>/dev/null; then
    useradd -m -s /bin/bash $NEWUSER
    echo "$NEWUSER:password123" | chpasswd
    echo "User $NEWUSER created."
fi
# Setup firewall with UFW (only allow SSH, HTTP, HTTPS)
ufw allow ssh
ufw allow http
ufw allow https
ufw --force enable
echo "Hardening completed!"

